                    <div class="box-body">
                        <p>Before using NickelTracker to record your expenses, you must setup your account.</p>

                        <h5><strong>1. Setup you Accounts</strong></h5>
                        <p>By default, the system creates 3 sample accounts for you: Cash, Debit and Credit. However,
                            you can (and should) create as many accounts as you have or use. It doesn't matter if you have more than one
                            account of any type. For example, if you have a Mastercard credit card and another Visa, you should
                            create a record for each one of them!</p>

                        <h5><strong>2. Setup your Categories</strong></h5>
                        <p>Think about the expenses you normally make during the month, and now try to group them into categories.
                        You can create as many categories as you'd like, but we've found that having no more than 15 works the best.</p>
                        <p>After you have created all your categories, then you must setup a budget for each one, or decide
                        how much you want to spend in that category each month. In some cases (rent, for example) you might already
                            know how much you have to spend, you can input that directly.</p>
                        <p>Although not recommended, it's okay to have categories with $0 budget, this way you will be able to at
                        least track your expenses in that.</p>

                        <h5><strong>3. Setup your initial balances</strong></h5>
                        <p>Check your balance in each of your accounts, and create a new Income Transaction record for each
                            account putting as "income" your current balance. If everything went okay, the <i class="fa fa-bank"></i>
                            Accounts screen should reflect your current balance across all of your accounts. As a tip, you can
                            set the date of these initial Income Transactions in the month before, so they don't mess up your
                            current month's statistics.</p>
                        <br>
                        <p>That's it! Start registering your transactions as soon as you make them!</p>
                    </div>
